<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,417,660]" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,391,489,516]" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">Natural history.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Daly" authorityYear="2004" box="[399,694,490,516]" class="Anthozoa" family="Actiniidae" genus="Isoaulactinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="21" pageNumber="172" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="hespervolita">
<emphasis box="[399,694,490,516]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">Isoaulactinia hespervolita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
inhabits the intertidal zone, in tide pools, attached to rocks, with remains of shells or rocks attached to the column (
<bibRefCitation author="Daly, M." box="[715,852,526,552]" pageId="21" pageNumber="172" pagination="377 - 390" refId="ref12886" refString="Daly, M. (2004 a) Anatomy and Taxonomy of three species of sea anemones (Cnidaria: Anthozoa: Actiniidae) from the Gulf of California, including Isoaulactinia hespervolita Daly, n. sp. Pacific Science, 3, 377 - 390. https: // doi. org / 10.1353 / psc. 2004.0030" type="journal article" year="2004">Daly 2004a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
